➜Teach grandparents to use mobile phones
http://www.sohu.com/a/437614997_162758	21709
<p><img src="http://p6.itc.cn/q_70/images03/20201211/c2664a75659f41dd81a821b146e56465.jpeg" /></p>
<p>On December 8, Shi Jiayi (left), a volunteer from Beijing Foreign Studies University, explains how to use smart phones to query health codes at the citizen activity center of Huayuan Road, Haidian District, Beijing. On the same day, during the "science and technology helping the elderly" activity of Huayuan Road community activity center in Haidian District, Beijing, college students volunteers from Beijing Foreign Studies University taught more than a dozen elderly people how to use smart phones, hand-in-hand to teach them how to register with smart phones and inquire about their health codes, so as to help them solve the problems encountered in their daily use of smart phones. Since 2014, Huayuan road street, Haidian District, Beijing, has cooperated with the social welfare organization Beijing sunset re morning social work service center to carry out the "science and technology assistance for the elderly" activity in the district. Through the science and technology lecture hall and the one-to-one "youth with sunset" mode, university volunteers from 18 colleges and universities have been led to teach computers, smart phones and other electronic technology products for the elderly in the neighborhood Basic use method, as well as online shopping, registration and other skills. Up to now, more than 240 activities have been carried out, serving more than 6000 community residents. Photo by Ju huanzong, a reporter from Xinhua News Agency Huang Yicheng (left), a volunteer from Beijing Foreign Studies University, explains the use of smart phone registration for the elderly at the public activity center of Huayuan road street, Haidian District, Beijing on December 8. （Photo by Ju huanzong/Xinhua News）</p>
